page.title: 01Hill area sth of Loch Tay
page.content: This is open, hilly counry rising steeply southwards from height 150m near the loch shore to over 500m. Trees are sparse. Thre ae two small copses near the centre of area. The hillsides are boggy, but there is some sheep grazing. Five small steams run from sth to north, including the Finglen Burn across Sq4 and the Allt Meall nan dam through sqs 10,6,7 and 3. The loch side road crosses the north west corner of area in sq 1 where there is a farm,and a farmtrack runs up southwards from village of Ardeonnnnaig half a mile to north, through sq 3, wehre there are two farms thats all. From hilltop in sq 5 thre is a superb view up eastern half of Loch Tay.
